<svg width="100%" viewBox="0 0 680 1060" role="img" style="" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
<title style="fill:rgb(0, 0, 0);stroke:none;color:rgb(255, 255, 255);stroke-width:1px;stroke-linecap:butt;stroke-linejoin:miter;opacity:1;font-family:&quot;Anthropic Sans&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;text-anchor:start;dominant-baseline:auto">AWS resource creation order and dependencies</title>
<desc style="fill:rgb(0, 0, 0);stroke:none;color:rgb(255, 255, 255);stroke-width:1px;stroke-linecap:butt;stroke-linejoin:miter;opacity:1;font-family:&quot;Anthropic Sans&quot;, -apple-system, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:400;text-anchor:start;dominant-baseline:auto">A layered diagram showing the order in which AWS resources must be created, from VPC foundation at the top through networking, security, data, compute templates, and finally load balancing and auto scaling at the bottom. Arrows point from each resource to the resource it depends on.</desc>
<defs>
